men, blamed others for any filing errors.</line></document><document name="LTW_ENG_20051018.0002"><line>Four months after Ney's remarks in the Congressional Record, Boulis was murdered in Fort Lauderdale.</line></document><document name="LTW_ENG_20050308.0163"><line>At the time of his Scotland trip in 2002, Ney of Ohio was attempting to amend a bill to aid an Abramoff tribal client in Texas.</line></document><document name="LTW_ENG_20051018.0002"><line>&quot;The new owner, Mr. Adam Kidan, is most well known for his successful enterprise, Dial-a-Mattress, but he is also well known as a solid individual and a respected member of his community.</line></document><document name="LTW_ENG_20050505.0164"><line>In an interview, Fitial called Buckham a longtime friend and said the former DeLay chief of staff offered to help and bring along Scanlon.</line><line>Despite congressional defeat of the wage and immigration legislation fought by Abramoff, the Marianas apparel industry has suffered another setback with elimination of tariffs on Chinese-made goods.</line></document><document name="NYT_ENG_20050418.0210"><line>A former Georgia GOP chairman, he was the Southeast regional campaign chairman for the Bush-Cheney 2004 presidential campaign.</line></document><document name="LTW_ENG_20050505.0164"><line>We need P &amp; G (Abramoff's law firm) to help save our economy....</line></document><document name="LTW_ENG_20051018.0002"><line>Tuohey has not returned phone calls in recent weeks to discuss his client.</line></document><document name="NYT_ENG_20050418.0210"><line>The firm forced him out a year ago when it discovered Abramoff had hidden at least $10 million from Indian clients.</line></document><document name="LTW_ENG_20050308.0163"><line>Times researcher Mark Madden contributed to this report.</line><line>Abramoff represented the territory and its apparel manufacturers at the time.</line></document><document name="LTW_ENG_20050505.0164"><line>Within months of the visit, Abra