e same restaurant.</line></document><document name="LTW_ENG_20050505.0164"><line>Following the visit of Buckham and Scanlon, Fitial took several steps to pressure the island government to renew and extend contracts with Abramoff's law firm.</line></document><document name="LTW_ENG_20051102.0151"><line>Rosetti recounted an incident in which, he said, Griles gave him a binder filled with letters and documents critical of the bid by the Jenna Band of the Choctaw Tribe to build a casino one hour from the Coushattas' $300-million-a-year casino.</line></document><document name="LTW_ENG_20050505.0164"><line>Neubauer reported from Washington.</line></document><document name="LTW_ENG_20051102.0151"><line>Two former high-level U.S. Interior Department officials clashed before a Senate committee Wednesday over whether one of them -- while still in his government post -- sought to pressure Interior Secretary Gale A. Norton on behalf of controversial lobbyist Jack Abramoff's tribal clients.<annotation scu-count="1" sum-count="1" sums="25"><scu uid="1" label="Jack Abramoff is a  GOP lobbyist" weight="4"/></annotation></line></document><document name="NYT_ENG_20050418.0210"><line>As a result, he has drawn some criticism.</line></document><document name="LTW_ENG_20050505.0164"><line>Scanlon's lawyer did not respond to similar questions.</line></document><document name="NYT_ENG_20050428.0261"><line>Upon his return, he declared dead a bill that Democrats had hoped to pass raising wages and controlling immigration in the Marianas.</line></document><document name="LTW_ENG_20050308.0163"><line>He said the lobbyist had been the victim of &quot;unfair attacks&quot; and that &quot;Mr. Abramoff can only hope that people will not rush to judgment based on negative and one-sided attacks.&quot;</line></document><document name="NYT_ENG_20050418.0210"><line>&quot;How would we know where the money was coming from?&quot;</line></document><document name="LTW_ENG_20050308.0163"><line>One of their former tribal clients has since filed a lawsuit alleging civil fraud.</line><line>He privately raised tens of thousands of dollars for private jets and boasted of setting up golf junkets, according to documents, congressional testimony and interviews.</line><line>Abramoff did not respond to questions for this story.</line></document><document name="LTW_ENG_20051018.0002"><line>Foxcom, which has since moved headquarters from Jerusalem to Vienna, Va., and been renamed MobileAccess Networks, lobbied for the job.</line><line>His Dial-a-Mattress franchise in the District of Columbia was in bankruptcy.</line></document><document name="LTW_ENG_20050308.0163"><line>Abramoff pocketed $21 million.</line></document><document name="NYT_ENG_20050418.0210"><line>&quot;I'm sure my name has been taken in vain before, so I'm not surprised,&quot; said the Texas senator.</line></document><document name="LTW_ENG_20050505.0164"><line>A longtime critic of Abramoff and DeLay's activities in the Pacific island territories, Miller renewed his recent call for an investigation of Abramoff by the House Resources Committee that oversees the region.<annotation scu-count="1" sum-count="4" sums="10,38,5,8"><scu uid="22" label="DeLay investigated for connection to Abramoff" weight="4"/></annotation></line></document><document name="LTW_ENG_20050308.0163"><line>At Abramoff's direction, they had hired and paid Scanlon $4.2 million and made campaign contributions of $300,000 to Ney and others.</line><line>In a June 7, 2002, e-mail to Tigua consultant Schwartz, Abramoff wrote of the upcoming Ney golf junket, saying it &quot;will be quite expensive (We did this for another member -- you know who) two years ago.&quot;</line><line>He said it was &quot;based on representations&quot; by Abramoff that the National Center sponsored their travel.</line></document><document name="NYT_ENG_20051102.0241"><line>But Michael Rosetti, former counsel to Interior Secretary Gale Norton, told the senators he repeatedly had to rebuff Griles' efforts to intervene.</line></document><document name="LTW_ENG_20051102.0151"><line>Abramoff has been indicted in federal court on six counts of fraud and conspiracy for his role in the 2000 purchase of a fleet of Florida gambling boats.</line></document><document name="LTW_ENG_20050505.0164"><line>But Fitial, still in the speaker post that DeLay's aides helped him win, has not given up.</line></document><document name="NYT_ENG_20050418.0210"><line>That was already a done deal,&quot; Cornyn said.</line></document><document name="LTW_ENG_20050505.0164"><line>Also, the island districts of the legislators who switched sides soon won federal budget benefits from Congress, apparently supported by DeLay.</line></document><document name="LTW_ENG_20050308.0163"><line>The National Center, in acknowledging its sponsorship of the DeLay trip in 2000, made no mention of golfing in Scotland.</line><line>Senators accused Abramoff and Scanlon of working both sides of the case -- secretly helping Christian conservative Ralph Reed persuade Texas state officials to close the Indian gambling center, then charging the Tigua tribe hefty fees to lobby for legislation to reopen it.<annotation scu-count="1" sum-count="1" sums="35"><scu uid="73" label="Ralph Reed implicated" weight="1"/></annotation></line></document><document name="LTW_ENG_20051018.0002"><line>These perks are used by House Republican leaders to keep their rank and file in line.</line></document><document name="LTW_ENG_20050308.0163"><line>Within weeks of midterm elections that gave the GOP control of the House, he left Hollywood and swapped his movie producer role to be a Capitol Hill lobbyist.</line></document><document name="LTW_ENG_20051102.0151"><line>But Republican lawmakers have been watching the Abramoff scandal unfold in the media and before the Indian Affairs Committee with particular dread, because the lobbyist had extensive connections with party officials and because his relentless pursuit of profit -- documented in a string of e-mails between Abramoff and his one-time partner, Michael Scanlon, that the committee has released -- casts an unflattering light on the role of lobbyists.</line></document><document name="NYT_ENG_20041001.0344"><line>That same tribe and another reportedly paid millions of dollars into... a self-proclaimed think tank run by two of Mr. Scanlon's beach buddies, one a yoga instructor, the other a lifeguard.&quot;</line></document><document name="LTW_ENG_20051018.0002"><line>Ney declined to be interviewed.</line></document><document name="NYT_ENG_20050418.0210"><line>Reed's company, Century Strategies, was paid by Scanlon's companies.</line></document><document name="LTW_ENG_20050505.0164"><line>In 2001, Fitial went to bat again for Abramoff, pressing to assure that the lobbyist's contracts were extended.</line></document><document name="LTW_ENG_20051018.0002"><line>He's going to do Tigua,&quot; Abramoff told Scanlon in a March 20, 2002, e-mail.<annotation scu-count="0" sum-count="1" sums="57"/></line></document><document name="APW_ENG_20051118.1118"><line>The acts, said the court papers, included &quot;agreements to support and pass legislation, agreements to place statements into the Congressional Record, meeting with Lobbyist A and Scanlon's clients, and advancing the application of Lobbyist A for a license to install wireless telephone infrastructure in the House of Representatives.&quot;</line></document><document name="LTW_ENG_20050308.0163"><line>He blamed the lobbyist.</line></document><document name="NYT_ENG_20050418.0210"><line>Cornyn said that he does not recall any contact with Abramoff and did not know that the lobbyist contributed $1,000 to his 2002 campaign.</line></document><document name="LTW_ENG_20050505.0164"><line>Abramoff told island officials that DeLay is &quot;our biggest supporter on Capitol Hill.&quot;</line></document><document name="APW_ENG_20051118.1118"><line>This typically is a prelude to a guilty plea and full cooperation with government investigators.</line></document><document name="LTW_ENG_20050505.0164"><line>Abramoff lost his CNMI contract in early 2002 when Juan Babauta took office as governor, having beaten several candidates including Fitial, the candidate of Abramoff and DeLay.<annotation scu-count="0" sum-count="2" sums="12,42"/></line></document><document name="LTW_ENG_20051018.0002"><line>LGC had no right to appeal.</line></document><document name="LTW_ENG_20050308.0163"><line>Abramoff's clients were among the leading opponents of that tax.</line><line>The Center describes itself as &quot;a communications and research foundation supportive of a strong national defense and dedicated to providing free market solutions to today's public policy problems.&quot;</line><line>The Senate Indian Affairs Committee is looking into allegations Abramoff and a former DeLay aide bilked six Indian tribes out of millions of dollars in lobbying and public relations fees.<annotation scu-count="2" sum-count="3" sums="13,21,43"><scu uid="20" label="Abramoff and Scanlon bilked clients of millions of dollars" weight="1"/><scu uid="20" label="Abramoff and Scanlon bilked clients of millions of dollars" weight="1"/></annotation></line></document><document name="LTW_ENG_20051018.0002"><line>&quot;It's crazy&quot; for Ney to say he was duped, Abramoff said.<annotation scu-count="0" sum-count="1" sums="57"/></line></document><document name="LTW_ENG_20051102.0151"><line>Rosetti said he had to press Griles to learn that the folder had been compiled by Abramoff.</line></document><document name="APW_ENG_20051118.1118"><line>DeLay, until recently one of the most powerful politicians in the United States, is not involved but is charged in an unrelated state campaign finance case in his native Texas.</line></document><document name="NYT_ENG_20050428.0261"><line>A woman answering the phone at Strategic Business Ethics in California, where Lapin is chief executive, said he could not be reached for comment because of the Passover holidays.</line></document><document name="LTW_ENG_20050505.0164"><line>A federal grand jury is now investigating.<annotation scu-count="1" sum-count="1" sums="13"><scu uid="71" label="Abramoff and Scanlon investigations led to other investigations" weight="1"/></annotation></line><line>For Palacios, it was assistance repairing a dilapidated, half century-old breakwater on the island of Tinian.</line><line>In a Jan. 4, 2001 letter seeking a renewal of his contract, Abramoff bragged of bringing the territory &quot;back from the brink of disaster....</line></document></collection>